        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to perform a specific calculation or transformation related to a \"meter constant,\" which is a term used in utility metering to convert raw meter readings into standardized units."
